{"type":"message","id":"5a6c82bb","parentId":"c71d9df7","timestamp":"2026-03-04T19:45:58.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has sent `/skill_creator` which suggests they want to use the skill-creator skill. Let me first complete my startup sequence by reading the required files, then I need to execute the skill.\n\nActually, wait - the user is explicitly triggering a command/skill. Let me re-read the instructions. The user says \"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now\" - so I need to read the required files first.\n\nLooking at the instructions:\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nThese are already in my context (injected as Project Context), so I should have them. Let me verify I have the key info:\n\nFrom the context:\n- SOUL.md is present - I know my core truths\n- USER.md is present - but it's empty (just template)\n- MEMORY.md is present - shows no previous sessions\n- BOOTSTRAP.md is present - this is a fresh workspace\n\nThe user also sent `/skill_creator` which seems to be a command to use the skill-creator skill. The skill is available based on the <available_skills> section.\n\nLet me first complete my startup greeting, then handle the skill_creator request.\n\nSince this is a new session and BOOTSTRAP.md exists, this is a fresh workspace. I should greet appropriately and then address the skill_creator command.\n\nActually, re-reading the instructions more carefully - I should \"read the required files before responding to the user\" but they're already in my context. The key instruction is to \"greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided.\"\n\nLooking at IDENTITY.md - it's empty (just template). \n\nSince there's no persona configured yet, I'll go with a natural, conversational greeting and then address what they want to do. The `/skill_creator` message is likely them invoking a command, so I should acknowledge that after the greeting.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Ollie! Fresh workspace, new session — let's make it count. What are we working on?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":12519,"output":479,"cacheRead":544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13542,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772653538397}}
{"type":"message","id":"79fb2c0e","parentId":"5a6c82bb","timestamp":"2026-03-04T19:46:00.140Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"36\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1734128684\",\n  \"sender\": \"ollie\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-04 19:45 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ollie (1734128684)\",\n  \"id\": \"1734128684\",\n  \"name\": \"ollie\"\n}\n```\n\nmy name is Ollie, your are kiloclaw"}],"timestamp":1772653560138}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b4977f9","parentId":"79fb2c0e","timestamp":"2026-03-04T19:46:07.074Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is telling me their name is Ollie and I'm called \"kiloclaw\". This is a bootstrap conversation - they're helping me figure out who I am.\n\nLet me update my identity files based on this. The user said my name is \"kiloclaw\" - that seems to be my name. Let me update IDENTITY.md and USER.md with what I've learned.\n\nWait - I should follow the BOOTSTRAP.md instructions. Let me read the skill creator skill first since that's what they asked about, then continue the bootstrap conversation naturally.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Nice to meet you, Ollie! \"Kiloclaw\" — I like that. Sounds sharp.\n\nSo I should read the skill_creator skill you mentioned — want me to do that now, or tell me more about what you need first?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":126,"output":165,"cacheRead":13060,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13351,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772653560140}}
